# Testing Guide

This project uses pytest for testing with high code coverage (>99%).

## Key Test Files

- **[tests/test_config.py](mdc:tests/test_config.py)**: Tests for configuration module
  - Environment variable handling
  - Validation functions
  - Error cases

- **[tests/test_main.py](mdc:tests/test_main.py)**: Tests for the main module
  - Device discovery
  - Connectivity checks
  - Output formatting
  - Exception handling

- **[tests/test_main_entry.py](mdc:tests/test_main_entry.py)**: Tests for the entry point logic
  - Module execution behavior
  - Command-line behavior

- **[tests/check_coverage.py](mdc:tests/check_coverage.py)**: Script for testing and verifying code coverage

## Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
python -m pytest

# Run tests with coverage report
python tests/check_coverage.py

# Run specific test files
python -m pytest tests/test_config.py
python -m pytest tests/test_main.py

# Run a specific test function
python -m pytest tests/test_main.py::test_check_host_connectivity_success
```

## Test Configuration

The pytest configuration in [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) specifies:
- Minimum pytest version
- Coverage reporting options
- Test paths
- Python file patterns for test discovery
